import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='x')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], c=data['distance'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between x and y?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar(label='distance')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], c=data['distance'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between distance and x or y?', wrap=True)
    cbar = plt.colorbar(scatter)
    cbar.ax.set_ylabel('Distance')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
